{{Year in Sri Lanka|1985}}

The following lists events that happened during '''[[1985]] in [[Sri Lanka]]'''.

==Incumbents==
*[[President of Sri Lanka|President]]: [[J. R. Jayewardene]] 

==Events==
*146 civilians are killed in the  Anuradhapura massacre occurred in Sri Lanka in 1985 and was carried out by the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam. This was the largest massacre of Sinhalese civilians by the LTTE to date.<ref>[http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,957036,00.html]</ref>
*The [[1985 Muttur massacre]] was the slaughter of Tamil civilians in the town of [[Muttur (Sri Lanka)|Muttur]] in [[Eastern Province, Sri Lanka]].  The attack was coordinated by the Sri Lankan Military leaving 30-100 dead (civilians and militants) 
*The Indian cricket team toured Sri Lanka from 25 August to 22 September 1985.
