'''Chuchle battle''' was a student brawl fought in a [[Chuchle]] restaurant on June 29, 1881, resulting in several wounds and a general [[hangover]], a swatch of [[Czech people|Czech]] and [[Germans|German]] [[chauvinism]] in the late 19th century, just before the [[Charles University|Charles-Ferdinand University]] was divided into  [[Czech Charles-Ferdinand University]] and [[German Charles-Ferdinand University]] part in 1882.

