The '''National Historic Lookout Register''' is a program administered by the [[United States Forest Service]], the [[Forest Fire Lookout Association]], the [[National Forestry Association]], the [[National Woodland Owners Association]], state forestry departments and [[United States Department of the Interior|Department of Interior]] agencies to recognize historic [[fire lookout tower]]s in the United States.<ref>{{cite press release |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=Four Grand Canyon National Park Lookout Towers have been listed on the National Historic Lookout Register |url=http://grandcanyon.areaparks.com/parkinfo.html?pid=13872 |location=Grand Canyon, Arizona |publisher= |agency=[[National Park Service]] |date=July 22, 2009 |access-date=December 9, 2015}}</ref> It was established in 1990.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.flickr.com/photos/blmoregon/albums/72157657804496821 | title=Pechuck Lookout | publisher=Bureau of Land Management Oregon and Washington | accessdate=December 9, 2015}}</ref>
